articles.author: Jasper Ward
articles.description: The two Israeli embassy staffers were committed to Israel-Palestinian dialogue and about to get engaged.
articles.title: Two Israeli embassy staffers shot dead in downtown Washington, lone suspect held

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: Flour and other food aid will start reaching some of Gaza's most vulnerable people after Israel let some trucks through, but nowhere near enough to make up for shortages caused by an 11-week blockade, Palestinian officials said.
articles.title: Some bread and baby food reach Gazans as blockade eases, Palestinians call for more

articles.author: Joey Roulette
articles.description: U.S. President Donald Trump's Golden Dome missile defense concept revives a controversial, decades-old initiative whose ambitious construction could upend norms in outer space and reshape relations between the world's top space powers.
articles.title: Trump's Golden Dome plan could launch new era of weapons in space

articles.author: Emily Rose
articles.description: The two young Israeli embassy employees killed by a gunman at a Jewish museum in Washington had big dreams of building bridges and promoting dialogue in the conflict-ridden Middle East, according to people who knew them.
articles.title: Israeli embassy staffers killed in Washington aspired to Middle East bridge-building

articles.author: Olivia Kumwenda-Mtambo, Alexander Winning
articles.description: Facing a barrage of debunked claims from U.S. President Donald Trump that white people were being persecuted in his country, South African President Cyril Ramaphosa remained composed, pushed back politely and even tried to joke with Trump.
articles.title: Buffeted by Trump, South Africa's Ramaphosa praised for keeping his cool

articles.author: Orhan Qereman
articles.description: Syrian Kurdish parties will send a delegation to Damascus soon for talks over their region's political future, a leading Kurdish politician said, as they seek to advance their goal of regional autonomy despite opposition from the Islamist rulers.
articles.title: Kurds plan Damascus talks as visions for Syria collide

articles.author: Louise Rasmussen, Jacob Gronholt-Pedersen
articles.description: Nine European countries, led by Italy and Denmark, will on Thursday call on the European Union to make it simpler for member states to expel foreign criminals, according to a letter seen by Reuters.
articles.title: European leaders to ask EU for easier expulsion of foreign criminals

articles.author: Andreas Rinke, Sarah Marsh
articles.description: Europe needs to step "out of its comfort zone" and consider much tougher sanctions on Russia, such as bans on gas or uranium, or tapping into frozen Russian state assets, Thorsten Frei, the chief of staff of Germany's new chancellor, told Reuters.
articles.title: New German chancellery chief calls for tougher Russia sanctions

articles.author: Muvija M, Michael Holden
articles.description: Britain can conclude a deal with Mauritius on the future of the Chagos Islands on Thursday after a judge at London's High Court overturned an eleventh-hour injunction which had blocked the agreement being signed earlier.
articles.title: UK court lifts injunction, allowing Chagos Islands deal to proceed

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The EU's top diplomat Kaja Kallas on Thursday said the bloc has begun to lift sanctions on Kosovo, but that the process would be conditional on a sustained de-escalation of violence and hostilities in the north.
articles.title: EU says it has begun to ease sanctions on Kosovo
